As our Backend Engineer, you are experienced in building APIs and database frameworks using scalable technology. You are someone who can implement elegant architecture solutions as well as build robust services and clean interfaces around them. You will be responsible for the development of server-side logic, definition, maintenance of database, ensuring high performance and responsiveness to requests from the front-end.

To give you a flavour of our current stack - we are using ReactJS, Python on Django, hosted on AWS and working towards CICD using CircleCI. As we scale, our stack will evolve and we’re looking for you to play a key role in growing our capabilities.

Hmlet is revolutionising the way real estate industry operates with technology. Our engineers, product managers and designers are responsible for building tools and experiences for members of our community who stay at co-living spaces we operate, landlords and internal teams. As we operate increasingly at scale, all of us are  excited to ship digital products that help bring co-living into the mainstream and change the way we live.

You will be responsible for:

  Design, develop, test, deploy, maintain and improve high-quality software
  Manage individual project priorities, deadlines and deliverables.
  

You will need these skills for this role:

  Tertiary qualifications in Computer Science/Engineering, similar technical field of study or relevant practical experience.
  Software development experience in one or more general purpose programming languages.
  Experience working with two or more from the following: web or mobile application development, Unix/Linux environments, machine learning, information retrieval, natural language processing, networking, and/or security software development.
  Working proficiency and communication skills in written and verbal English.
